NEW YORK (AP) _ LivePerson Inc. (LPSN) on Thursday reported a loss of $49.9 million in its fourth quarter.The New York-based company said it had a loss of 70 cents per share. Losses, adjusted for stock option expense and amortization costs, were 41 cents per share.The results surpassed Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of six analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for a loss of 49 cents per share.The customer-service technology company posted revenue of $123.8 million in the period, also surpassing Street forecasts. Seven analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $123.7 million.For the year, the company reported that its loss widened to $125 million, or $1.80 per share. Revenue was reported as $469.6 million.For the current quarter ending in April, LivePerson said it expects revenue in the range of $124.6 million to $126.8 million.ADVERTISEMENTThe company expects full-year revenue in the range of $544.8 million to $563.3 million._____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on LPSN at https://www.zacks.com/ap/LPSN